The smart grid market is segmented based on components, deployment, and technology. By component, the market is categorized into solutions and services. The solution segment includes software and hardware components required for the smart grid infrastructure, while services encompass maintenance, consulting, and integration services. In terms of deployment, the market is further divided into generation, transmission, and distribution. Generation segment focuses on integrating renewable energy sources and optimizing power generation processes. The transmission and distribution segments emphasize efficient power transmission and supply to end-users. Regarding technology, the market includes smart metering, SCADA (Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition), demand response systems, and other advanced technologies aimed at enhancing grid efficiency and reliability. These segments collectively contribute to the growth and development of the smart grid market globally.

